caption: An odd selection of Pinball machines that normally would be awful, but works here.
Fun place!
One of many arcade bars across Chicago, but very fun on the weekends. Solid beers on tap.
Great bar. Fun arcade. We always have extra tokens left over.
Cool place but the amount of games is disappointing.
I think the Wicker Park one is cooler though.
Upbeat vibe with a DJ on Friday night. Games played with tokens. Drinks. An adult playground.
Smaller than their other locations, but still pretty good?
Great fun younger crowd but plenty of games to play. 2 pool tables didn't wait long to play. Great selection of beers. No food but you can bring your own or have it delivered there.

Although it's smaller than most beercades I've been to, it scratches the itch.  The service was great and there was always something to play.  My faves are Fooseball, Superchex (aka bubble hockey) and skee ball.  There aren't a ton of arcade games, but I got sucked into Rampage, just like back in the day.  There's also a handful of pinball games against a wall, but playing those games just reiterated how lousy of a player I am.  I guess you can't always dodge the truth.
Cool atmosphere, a great place to hang out with friends
Great drinks and fun games
So fun lots of old school games!
Much smaller and less offerings than the other 2 locations in Chicago

Good not great. Bartenders were fine, beer is beer. Place was definitely presentable and in line with neighborhood standards. Not enough games for an arcade (beercade). Fulton market = no parking. Still a great place to just stop in for a beer just wouldn't make a night out of it.

Casual and fun bar. Tired of your plain old bars with bad beers? The Emporium not only has some cool games to play for very cheap (played games for 2 hours for $10), but they also have a good selection of craft beers. Great spot to go after dinner.
Sooo fun! We played a few rounds of pool with friends and strangers!
Great bubble hockey machine
If you get $20 in quarters, you're playing for a long, long time.
Good atmosphere  and drinks and arcade
Great staff. Galaga. Kicker. Skee ball. Air Hockey. Pool. All the things I need!

Fun spot with full bar and classic arcade games. There are a few pool tables, air hockey tables, foosball tables and it's open late.  The vibe is chill and the place attracts all types of people.  There were people in there having fun in their gala dresses and others in jeans.  The DJ played some great new and classic hip hop (it was Saturday night).
Some of the games are broken, or faulty, otherwise good.
Very disappointed that some of the games were broken.  NBA Jam and Rescue 911.  Some others were also in average condition.
It's an ok place.  I like retro games, but it's always so doggone crowded and you cant get to the games!

Such a fun bar! The games and the drinks are very reasonably priced! We came here after a work holiday dinner and we had such a blast! Cant wait to come back again ^_^ I still have some leftover coins!
Cool little bar with old school hip hop. The games are not that great but it's a fun place to stop by and kill some time if you're in the area.

The drinks are cheap relative to other bars in the area but the place itself was tiny.  Most of the games in there had something wrong with them, from broken joysticks to machines not working altogether.  The game selection was also pretty small and a lot of staple games you'd expect to be in an arcade, like say street fighter 2, were absent from this place.  There are other better beercades including the other emporium locations
Fun playing games while drinking. Appeals to that generation who still remembers arcades before modern tech took over

Fun bar with a lot of selection but the games were pretty rough when I was there. Most pins had issues and some of the cabinets had monitor problems and loose stearing wheels. The token system makes no sense considering everything is one token. At a quarter a play just make it free. It's a bad attempt at customer retention that isn't necessary. Overall if you want to hangout and play air hockey it is great if you want to enjoy arcade games it isn't always the best.
Fun games
Great beer, great games, great people
Fun and chill spot with fun games and average drinks.
A few of the games were in disrepair but otherwise a good experience. Pinball has best selection

So fun! Great games and if one of them ate a token, the staff was super cool about helping you out. Good beer too! Went after brunch on a Saturday. A small birthday party came in not long after us with a wee baby. Seems to be family and friend friendly. 😉
Definitely one of the smallest Emporiums.
Good energy. Good vibes. Good peoples.
Fun little place to go for a quick drinks and some games.
Smaller than the original, beer choices are bad,they just have over priced cocktails. Uptight vibe compared to the original.
There weren't many games and it was really loud

This is a OLD SCHOOL ARCADE GAMES dream! There's games such as pac-Man, pinball, nba 1990, billiards, air hockey, fusball and many more.  Each game takes tokens about one to two.  We used $5 and got about 20 tokens. This venue is strictly 21+ and have a vast menu of cocktails. This place is great to attend after dinner and drinks with friends.
Very good beer and arcade, do you need more? This place is almost perfect. I love it.
Friendly employees and okay selection of games. Can't go wrong with this place if you have a date or a group.
Some games have issues other than that a nice place to hangout with friends

Fun vibe, pretty good drinks menu, and prices aren’t outrageous considering it’s the West Loop. Great place for a date! Got $10 worth of tokens and probably only ended up using half so we’ll have some for next time!
Fun arcade bar, chill vibe
Fun place
Games, drinks, good times.
Great fun for people in my age group. All the games we played as kids with a cocktail. Check Groupon for deals. Great first date spot.
Too many suits trying to be cool
Nice environment,friendly people, great games, and good drinks. Parking is scarce. It was my 1st time at this location but, I'll definitely be back. Oh Monday-Thursday 4-7pm is happy hour.
Great arcade bar located at the West Loop! It has some cool pinball options.
Loved hanging out here for a couple of beers and some games!

(Translated by Google) Many restaurants and bars are here. Also for the super rich of Chicago :-) Lamborginis and Porsches take turns.  (Original) Viele Restaurants und Bars sind hier. Auch für die Superreichen Chicagos :-) Lamborginis uns Porsches wechseln sich ab.

Its possible my feelings on this location are tainted because I went for an after work vibe and it was nearly empty. It didnt start filling up until 9p on a Thursday. That said, the games as always are great, but the drinks are lacking. There wasn't a beer I was particularly excited about and the prices were a buck or so higher than I'd like, but it's the new West Loop. The cocktails are a sore spot. I ordered a "Blame It On the Juice" for $13 and it came out an intense aquamarine color and tasted of bad energy drink. I wouldn't come again.
(Translated by Google) Yupp  (Original) Yupp

I had $10 in tokens, and left with $4. Outfitted with pool tables, air hockey, pin ball, skeet ball, and arcade games; there was enough fun to go around. Great place to throw a few drinks back, while watching a sporting event, and playing some classic arcade games.
Old video games for a little nostalgia. Got love it. And the beer selection is great as well.
Great fun spot.
Nothing like it.
Great spot, open late, loads of fun
Fix your air conditioning. Nobody is going to stick around in heat like that.
Lots of pinball machines and some great old school arcade machines. They also have billiards, air hockey, and Foosball. Also, the bar is huge and serves great drinks!
Fun place to check out
We had the best time here, loads of snooty bars nearby and this is where we hung out most

Came here last night to celebrate a friend's 21st birthday. Atmosphere was good, and the games are well maintained. Only 1 air hockey table had issues. Most importantly the service from the bartenders was AMAZING, both when I was sitting at the bar and when I came up for drinks. Never went long with an empty drink in my hand. The male bartender especially was very nice and very attentive, drinks were very good. The space here is a little smaller than other Emporiums but we had a great time!
It is what it is. Skeeball is great
Amazing!! Great music and great atmosphere!!

Drinks okay, good variety of games. Pool ends up being ruled by a couple of teams. Should have house rules that must be followed unless stated upfront. Also singles on a pool table on a Friday night? What is up with that?

This is going to be what I call a *qualified* five-star rating; selection and amount of games (especially pinball) better than what you'd expect from a smaller storefront like this, but their beer selection is more limited than Wicker Park's drafts and Logan Square's cans, and the floor layout nearly had me tripping walking up to the riser where the pinball machines are or getting elbowed by pool players when I walked past. Still a lot of fun, though.
Great selection of games and beer. Games tend to be down for a while if they break.

Really wouldn't recommend this place. Air hockey and skee ball tables are breaking, limited game selection, and you have to pay for the games. It may be a convenient location, but I'd suggest going to Replay on the West Side. Wider selection and the majority of their games are free. Really had too expectations for this place.
Super fun old games! Outside area is nice when the weather's warm.

The service here is god awful. Nobody greeted us and the bartender looked offended when we were asking for help with getting a table, since there was nobody was around. Come here for the games, that's it. Everything else is just trash.

Decent beer selection at the end of the day but only 6 on tap at the moment of this writing. Mix of arcade games, pool tables, air hockey, etc leaves options for everyone. Great vibes all around and caters to Fulton market.
Fun casual place with old games...good vibe all having fun
Great place for drinks n games
Good place just for short time. Not many pool tables. Overall it is just ok
Good food

If you like games, pool and skiball. This emporium is the palce for you. It has an open concept which is pretty cool. Great beer selection and the staff is very friendly. Deff stop in for some tmnt nostaligia via the footclan Hangouts. Read em and weep..full-house. awesome beer selection :)
Not as good as replay, worth checking out though.

Cheap beer, nice pool tables, can find tokens all over the bar, love that there are so many game options. Love the glowing designs all over the walls. Really like the photo booth and the bathroom! So cool!
you would expect more life in the atmosphere.. it's very dark, dirty, sticky & bland. More than a handful of the games didn't work. Drinks were made super WEAK
Wonderful memories reside there for me... Seriously go make some of your own!!!... Overall 8/10
Love this place. It took two days of rest afterwards
Several games out of order. Place seemed unfinished. Not a lot of game choices either.
Fun place, great arcade games, pinball machines,  pool,  table hockey and Notre the have skeeball. This place brings back memories
Nothing compared to the other emporiums but good to have near me
Great games and good drinks. $10 Worth of tokens gets you a long way
Great place for a birthday party! From airhockey to pinball, they have a nice selection of games. Just beware that space can be tight, especially after 8-9 pm.
Great place to just hang out and have some adult fun at night
A great bar for drinking and playing games
Drinks are over priced
Not as good as headquarters. You have to pay for the games here. Drink choices are very limited. Not a bad place, but not for me
Great interactive date spot

Fun games and a good bar. Two pool tables that seem to be too busy. This place could use a third one. Games take tokens and there are exchange machines so bring cash or your debit card. There is an ATM. Games are about 50 cents each. There are air hockey tables, fooseball, skeeball, racing arcade games, pinball and a ton of other machines. There is some kind of hockey game right in between two bathrooms. Silly placement and an awkward place to play. Drinks are good, games are inexpensive, and service is prompt. I will come back!

So fun! Great games and if one of them ate a token, the staff was super cool about helping you out. Good beer too! Went after brunch on a Saturday. A small birthday party came in not long after us with a wee baby. Seems to be family and friend friendly. 😉
Super fun bar, lots of games, and good prices!
fun barcade with lots of games!

I went on a very crowded night, so I'll give it the benefit of the doubt for that. Very hard to get to the bar to order, long waits for lines, and a few games broke while I was there. I'm sure it's more fun when there's some elbow room!

What a great spot! We stopped in after a bite at Kuma's, and had an awesome time. Some of the games were down, but that is to be expected. Bar service was fast, and there was a good selection for games.

Good games and decent pool tables.   The beer selection leaves something to be desired.  It is a little weird.  One would expect miller, Coors, Budweiser in what is clearly a blue collar bar that is verging in a dive bar.  They seem to have  mixed sense of their identity.
Has a little less personality than the other Emporium locations but still has the good beer selection and lots of game options
50 cent pool
Awesome atmosphere. A ton of fun!
Coolest place to be in the west loop.
TMNT Arcade
Who doesn't love well maintained arcade bars?
Nice place. Nice games!
A very fun place. Old vintage games. Like Pac man. Pinball machines.
Cool place, nice cocktails with funny names and awesome games. Bartender could have been nicer but maybe that was just supposed to be the vibe. Will go back anyway!
Great and fun place!
Fun place for drinks and games.
Tasty beverages
Nice spot but a bit smaller than the other emporiums
Definitely a fun place for gamers and anyone trying to enjoy a drink while gaming.

Emporium in Fulton Market is not as big as some other Emporiums but it is a great place to stop after or before lunch at one of the excellent restaurants in the area. A game of pool is only $0.50, and they also have air hockey and foosball in addition to the arcade and pinball games. A good variety to play for a small space. We had a good time!

Went for a night out with my bestfriend. This was my 1st time here and I was completely blown away! EMPORIUM ROCKS! It was so amazing. The atmosphere fun and the place is lined with games (all the old favorites). Need I say more....when in Chicago, Emporia is a must!!!
Cool place
Awesome. Great environment!!!!

This is a fun place to hang out at.  There are so many different types of games you could play- arcade, ping pong, bowling, VR, darts, etc.  Some are free and others you have to pay for. You can get tables to sit down to eat and drink.  They do offer event packages if you wanted to have your birthday or work event here. It gets crazy busy on weekend so there is a wait for a lot of the games. Service isn't the best but I don't think most people are here for food/drink service.
Always a fun spot!
Had a great time!! Had a lot of games to choose from.
Cool little arcade bar. Doesn't beat one in indy, but would recommend if you need something to do
Great games great staff
Fun time if your looking to play old school video games and new music. However I think sometimes the music is so loud you have to scream to talk to anyone.
Awsome place fun and entertaining
Air hockey!!!
Beer selection sucks in this place and so does the service. Bartender could smile more rather than trying to look tough! Video games could be better.
The concept is great. The execution is poor. The games are broken and take your money. The drinks are overpriced. It has the feel of an expensive dive bar. Two words that should never go together.
Game room with a bar fuse ball, air hockey, Pac man.
Smaller but nice. Didn't even know there were 3. Who knows how many more there are haha
Sack of garbage
Great place and fun:) Can not recommend the cocktails but they have nice craft beers on draft
Always
Service here is mediocre, once they find out you have a groupon they do not want to be bothered, and most of the gsmes were not working

If you love to drink and play old video games and pinball, this is the place to be. They are all pretty old games so some machines tend to eat up tokens but the staff there were more than happy to give free tokens back to you if you mention that the game ate your tokens.
Don’t have NFL blitz and NBA jam has one broken joystick.
Not as fun as other locations. Not a friendly crowd. All business no pleasure.

The beer selection was pretty good and the cocktail menu looked really diverse as well (although I did not try any). We spent a couple of hours there playing games. I wish they had a few more old school arcade games but overall the place is in a great spot, the service was good, and I liked the atmosphere.
Great place to do something more than just drink!

Bar and gameroom atmosphere was great.  Ther floors were wet from spilled drinks that required more attention.  The girl bar tender with the scissors tattoo not the friendliest or most helpful person. Good way to kill a couple of hours of fun time.
Great location and always fun with multiple billiards tables and air hockey tables, but it does have fewer arcade games than their other locations.
Very crowded, very hot, wish there were better games.
Great pinball machines, 2 pool tables

Great place good drinks vintage arcade games
Great selection and super nice bartenders. Shout out to Curtis ;)
Always a fan of emporium bars and this is no expeception. Great music and games. Beer list is always good and cocktails aren't bad either.

This place sucks. The pool tables jam and don't dispense the balls  all the time. The beer sucks and is over priced. Multiple of the games like the hockey games don't work half the time. Not coming back. Headquarters is better.
Awesome! Just like all the other Emporiums. This one can get kind of full quick so just be aware that the space is smaller but still have a blast every time we go.
Have to pay for games 🤮
This place is fun! You do have to pay for all the games. I came on a Saturday and the DJ was actually great if not a little loud for an arcade bar
Fun place, good vibes, easy parking, but could have better beer selection.

I've fallen in love. There wasn't a cover and games are 1 token or $.25 each. Decent game selection. Went on a saturday evening and the music selections were 90s and early 2000s hip hop. It is byof. Also there is a photobooth thats $5.

This place is so much fun! Original games and pin ball machines. Dj on site. It was quite cramped. A lot of people in the place. Wait for pool and air hockey tables. They have their own beers and then PBR. No food. Not for kids
Good games and beer.
It's a great place,perfect to kill some time before your reservation at one of the nearby restaraunts

Really good game bar for pinball and some retro arcade games.  Everything takes tokens, but even the pins (which are mostly in very good shape) are only one token, and the free credit thresholds are set very low.
I had such a blast on my date. It was so live and they have a bunch of arcade games with a whole food truck inside. It was a wonderful experience. I’m going back!
Cool place to play some vintage games or foos ball.
Books up quickly so make a group reservation well in advance if you need a table.
Arcade games and great draft beer?! What more can you ask for. West loop needed more casual bars and emporium is a welcome addition to the neighborhood
Great stop for my buddies bachelor party!
Nice space
Good beer selection, I dropped it a star because it has very few games
Very loud
Great spot after work. Love Curtis the bartender.

Cool concept and great new addition to The Fulton Market District.  Games are extremely cheep. Exchange dollars for tokens once you arrive ($1 = 4 tokens) and play dozens of arcade and video games. Table games (pool, air hockey, foosball, …
Local beer and fun arcade games in the Fulton market area! Photo booth and fun decor!
Waited an hour for a meatball.  Never got it.  Edit: This review was for "The Betty" which has since closed.  Same address, and some ownership share, so I guess Google kept it.
Drinks a little high lot's of games especial pinball just wish it had more of the classics
Beatty better by a mile.
Lots of fun. Kind of crowded compared to Wicker Park location.  Still a good time.
Great atmosphere. Bartenders were awesome too.!!

4 stars because the music was the right volume that I could easily hold a conversation the whole time I was there, which almost never happens. Because of this if definitely go back. Visited on a Thursday and service at the bar got a little slow after a huge crowd showed up at the same time around 10:00. Be aware that video games require tokens, which require cash to purchase. Not surprisingly almost no one was playing the games. (-1 star for slow service and having to pay for games)
Prices are higher then other locations, which is to be expected.  Draft and bottle list smaller than I would have thought though.  Good local beers, just wish they had a bigger selection
